All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    DiscoveryResponse
    This telegram is send by all SMA devices that support the speedwire protocol if they receive a discovery request.
    For sending discovery requests, use Speedwire.sendDiscoveryRequest()
    EnergyMeterChannels
    This interface provides a collection of all measuring channels supported by SMA Energy Meters and SMA Sunny Home Manager (2.0), as well as the units of the measurements.
    EnergyMeterTelegram
    A telegram from an SMA Energy Meter or an SMA Sunny Home Manager (2.0)
    InvalidTelegramException
    Indicates an error while parsing a telegram.
    This may be because the telegram does not match the type that is tried to parse or because it was corrupted.
    MeasuringChannel<Q extends javax.measure.Quantity<Q>>
    All measured data is divided into channels.
    This class defines the identifier, the description, the unit and the physical quantity of a channel.
    OBISIdentifier
    OBIS identifiers are used to identify measurement values in a telegram.
    They are defined in the ICE 62056-61 standard.
    Speedwire
    Main class for interacting with speedwire devices.
    SpeedwireCallback
    The callback that is run on any received data packets over sma speedwire.
    SpeedwireErrorHandler
    The callback that is run on any occurring exceptions while reading incoming packets from sma speedwire.
    Telegram
    Data received via speedwire is called telegram.
    On construction of a telegram the data is validated and parsed.
